%h1 Docs

:markdown
  Welcome to the new Rhomobile docs!  Browse around the [docs](/home) on the left and checkout our tutorials below to get started.  

  These docs are also [open source](http://github.com/rhomobile/rhomobile-docs), so please fork the project and provide feedback if you want to add content or find errors.

%h2 Tutorials
%ul
  :plain
    <li><a href="/rhodes/tutorial">Rhodes Tutorial:</a> A brief tutorial that shows how to install and use Rhodes and RhoSync to build smartphone apps.  Start here!</li>
    <li><a href="/rhosync/tutorial">RhoSync Tutorial:</a> Shows you how install RhoSync and write a source adapter to easily integrate with backend apps.</li>
    <li><a href="/rhohub/tutorial">RhoHub Tutorial:</a> Intro to RhoHub, which shows how you build smartphone apps online and provide hosted sync.</li>
    <li><a href="/thirdparty-tutorials">Third Party Tutorials:</a> Several third party tutorials, including Japanese translations of our documentation.</li>
    <li><a href="http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/documentation/quickstart">Ruby in Twenty Minutes:</a> You can do much with Rhodes with no prior Ruby. But this tutorial is helpful as you modify controllers.</li>

